include ../common/mixins.pug

div.staticPage
    h3 Art of Reading
    img.left(src="assets/chicken.png" alt="" width="164" height="150")/
    div
        strong: em The Art Of Reading Free Edition
        |  is an optional addition to
        +link("https://software.sil.org/wesay") WeSay
        |  and
        +link("/landing") Bloom
        |  that gives you easy access to over 10,000 black &amp; white illustrations from around the world, now with an even more permissive Creative Commons license,
        +link("https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/") BY-SA.
    br
    div
        +link("https://s3.amazonaws.com/bloomlibrary.org/ArtOfReading/ArtOfReading-Free-Setup3.3.exe") Download Art Of Reading version 3.3 Installer
        |  (320 Megabytes, for Microsoft Windows)
        br
        | For WeSay before 1.6 and Bloom before 4.0, use this
        +link("https://s3.amazonaws.com/bloomlibrary.org/ArtOfReading/ArtOfReading3.1FreeSetup.exe") older version (3.2).

    br
    div
        | For Linux, assuming you have followed the
        +link("/installers/linux") instructions for installing bloom on Linux
        | , you just need one more command:

        pre sudo apt-get install art-of-reading
    br
    h5 Metadata

    div
        | A special feature of this package is that we have embedded, in the image files themselves, information on where they came from, what their license is, etc. This will allow programs to help you make sure you are using the images legally.
    br
    h5 Note
    div
        | This is not the full "
        +link("https://www.ethnologue.com/show_product.asp?isbn=9781556712418") International Illustrations: The Art Of Reading
        | ". That product, which comes as a DVD, includes 3rd-party commercial software for finding the image you want. In contrast, the package offered here contains only the images themselves, and is only useful when used from a program that can help you find images (namely WeSay and Bloom).
